The couple were shot dead in the street by Gavrilo Princip, 19. He was a Bosnian Serb student and revolutionary who was opposed to the Austrian occupation. The murder triggered a chain of events which would ultimately lead to the outbreak of the First World War.  62 years ago (1960) The BBC opened its new Television Centre at White City, west London. Described as the Taj Mahal of TV, it was the largest dedicated TV centre in the world. It housed seven studios, the largest being the 11,000sq ft Studio One. The centre closed its doors back in 2013.  48 years ago (1974) Ballet dancer Mikhail Baryshnikov defected from the Soviet Union to Canada while on tour. He joined the New York City Ballet as a principal dancer before becoming an artistic director and branching out into film and TV.